<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.list(page=0, page_size=100)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:
```

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\} \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[], stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/history \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all entries in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the entries belonging to that conversation. The entries are sorted in the order they were appended, those can be messages, connectors or function_call.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/messages \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all messages in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the messages belonging to that conversation. This is similar to retrieving all entries except we filter the messages only.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_messages(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", from_entry_id="<id>", stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

Python

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start_stream(inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "function.result",
            "tool_call_id": "<id>",
            "result": "<value>",
        },
    ], stream=True)

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "message.input",
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "<value>",
            "prefix": False,
        },
    ], from_entry_id="<id>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```
